com.martinandersson.money.lib.serializer

Enum SerializationFramework

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<SerializationFramework>
      • com.martinandersson.money.lib.serializer.SerializationFramework
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializer, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<SerializationFramework>

    public enum SerializationFramework
extends java.lang.Enum<SerializationFramework>
implements Serializer
    Provides the Serializer implementation of all known serialization frameworks used in this project:
    • Java
    • Kryo Vanilla
    • Kryo Custom
    • FST Vanilla
    • FST Custom
    "Vanilla" versions of a serialization framework will serialize/deserialize using the framework "out of the box".

    "Custom" variants will configure the framework to use custom serializers for an even smarter serialization/deserialization protocol.

    Both Kryo and FST can be configured beyond all sanity when it comes to serialization/deserialization. I try to stick to as much vanilla flavor as possible. For example, both Kryo and FST support internal use of sun.misc.Unsafe and both support the ability to not reuse objects but always create new instances. Even though the latter configuration actually make sense for our domain model (since all our prices and the fields within them represents truly unique objects), none of these configuration night hacks has been applied.

      • JAVA

        public static final SerializationFramework JAVA
        This serializer uses the JDK provided ObjectOutputStream and ObjectInputStream to serialize/deserialize.

        The objects themselves may customize this protocol (Serializable) or fully replace it (Externalizable).

      • KRYO_CUSTOM

        This serializer uses a customized version of Kryo for serialization/deserialization.

        Kryo has been customized with serializers that is a bit smarter than vanilla Kryo when it comes to marshalling objects. See KryoSerializers.
